cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks on deep neural networks, which is a common concern in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a novel adversarial training objective that is similar to GANs, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses generative models to define detection/classification models, which is related to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
